# Enterprise Active Directory Home Lab

## Overview

This project documents the deployment of an enterprise-style Active Directory environment using Windows Server 2008 R2, Windows 7 clients, Kali Linux, and Oracle VirtualBox.

The objective was to simulate a corporate network by deploying Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS), configuring DNS, joining client systems to the domain, and performing LDAP enumeration from a security testing perspective.

---

## Objectives

- Deploy Windows Server as an Active Directory Domain Controller.
- Configure integrated DNS for Active Directory.
- Configure static IP addressing.
- Join Windows client systems to the domain.
- Create users, groups, and Organizational Units (OUs).
- Verify domain authentication.
- Perform LDAP enumeration from Kali Linux.
- Document the deployment and troubleshooting process.

---

## Lab Environment

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Hypervisor | Oracle VirtualBox |
| Domain Controller | Windows Server 2008 R2 |
| Client | Windows 7 |
| Attacker Machine | Kali Linux |
| Services | Active Directory, DNS, LDAP |
| LDAP Port | 389 |

